Abstrak:
In its first major result, just over a year after it began operating, a super-sensitive South
African telescope has discovered two giant ‘radio bubbles’ above and below the central
region of the Milky Way. The features stretch over a total of 430 parsecs (1,400 light years), about 5% of the distance between the Solar System and the Galaxy’s centre
Fakultas: Fakultas Matematika dan Ilmu Pengetahuan Alam
